During those tense moments at the bar, I did slap my boyfriend in the face in a moment of anger. I deeply regret resorting to physical force, but I did not cause any further harm. I recognize the fear and distress my behavior may have caused to those present in the bar, and for that, I am truly sorry.

In mitigating my offense, I would like to bring to the court's attention several factors. Firstly, I have no prior criminal record. This demonstrates that my actions on that day were an unfortunate anomaly, rather than a pattern of behavior. Secondly, I have been actively attending therapy sessions once a week as part of my commitment to personal growth and self-improvement.

Lastly, I want to express the significant remorse and regret I feel for my actions. I understand the gravity of my offense, and I sincerely apologize to all those who were affected by my behavior in the bar that night. I have reflected on my actions and understand the need for a better approach to handling my emotions.

Your Honor, I respectfully submit that I have taken responsibility for my actions, and I am committed to making amends and becoming a better member of society. I sincerely plead for leniency in sentencing, understanding that the court must uphold the law and ensure justice prevails.

Thank you for considering my statement. I humbly request your mercy.

Respectfully,

Chloe Mills

